  "prompt": "Is morning sickness a sign of good pregnancy?",
  "response": "Morning sickness, which includes nausea and sometimes vomiting, is a common symptom experienced by many (but not all) pregnant individuals, particularly in the first trimester. While it can be uncomfortable, morning sickness is often considered a positive sign of a healthy pregnancy. Here\u2019s why:\n\n1. **Hormonal Indicators**: Morning sickness is linked to the rise in pregnancy hormones, particularly **human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG)** and **estrogen**. Higher levels of these hormones are associated with a thriving pregnancy.\n\n2. **Lower Risk of Miscarriage**: Studies have shown that women who experience morning sickness are less likely to have a miscarriage compared to those who don\u2019t. This suggests that the presence of these symptoms may indicate a healthy, well-developing pregnancy.\n\n3. **Healthy Placenta Development**: Morning sickness is thought to be a sign that the placenta is producing the necessary hormones to support the pregnancy.\n\nThat said, it\u2019s important to note:\n- **Not Everyone Experiences Morning Sickness**: The absence of morning sickness does not mean the pregnancy is unhealthy. Many women have perfectly healthy pregnancies without nausea or vomiting.\n- **Severe Morning Sickness**: If nausea and vomiting are excessive (a condition called **hyperemesis gravidarum**), it can lead to dehydration and other complications, so medical attention may be needed.\n\nIf you have concerns about your pregnancy or symptoms, it\u2019s always best to consult your healthcare provider for personalized advice.",
